column2: Average Scheduled Monthly Payments for New Mortgage Loans ($)
Canada, Provinces, and CMAs,  2012 Q3  to 2025 Q2
Seasonal effects have not been removed from the data
Monthly payments are in unadjusted Canadian Dollars
The account's open date is within the past three months.

In the case of mortgage accounts certain cases could arise: (i.) a new date is given when a new mortgage is financed, (ii.) a borrower refinances their mortgage loan with a new lender, (iii.) a borrower refinances with same lender at higher ammount.
Equifax data aligns with Statistics Canada's definitions of Census Metropolitan Areas (CMAs).
For further information on CMA definition consult this link: https://www12.statcan.gc.ca/census-recensement/2011/ref/dict/geo009-eng.cfm
Charlottetown, PEI, is not classified as a CMA yet.  It has been included in this analysis to ensure broad representation of all of Canada's markets.
